\begin{frame}{Matera}
\begin{itemize}
    \item\small is the third most ancient city of the world, also known as "\textbf{the city of the Sassi}", because of the peculiarity and uniqueness of its historic center, declared a world heritage site by UNESCO in 1993, which is made up of rock buildings and architecture dug into the rock.
    \item\small the choice of the site for the town caused difficulties in supplying water, but since ancient times a complex system of water canalization, cisterns and "divers" was created, appearing to be one of the oldest and best preserved examples of \textbf{bio-architecture} in the world.
    \item\small In the late 1950s for irrigation purposes, the Bradano river was interrupted by the building of a dam, called \textbf{Lake San Giuliano}. 
\end{itemize}
\end{frame}

